*** note: may need to include sudo before every command
    also run these commands in the root folder ***

*** working- websocket container, backend api server, need to npm start in terminal ***
*** in progress- figuring out front end ***


*** front end (takes care of npm start) *** --- WIP
docker build -f ./docker_files/front_end.Dockerfile -t front_end --no-cache .
docker run -t -d -p 3000:3000 front_end

*** back end (takes care of node apiserver) *** --- works
docker build -f ./docker_files/back_end.Dockerfile -t back_end --no-cache .
docker run -t -d -p 4000:4000 back_end

*** websocket (takes care of node websocketserver) --- works
docker build -f ./docker_files/websocket.Dockerfile -t websocket --no-cache .
docker run -t -d -p 8080:8080 websocket

*** to stop container ***
docker container stop <container id>


*** other useful commands ***
** show all containers (processes running and stopped)
docker ps -a 

** remove stopped container, add -f arg to force it to stop and remove **
docker rm <container id>

** show docker images **
docker image ls

** remove image **
docker rmi <image id>

** when you edit docker files, should remove old images and rerun the build and run stuff **
** also remove old containers **
